stylometry: Optimization is when you are trying to find a way to maximize your profits or minimize your costs while staying within your contraints. An example of this is how Wal-mart buys products at a very low cost and sets the price at a certain markup percent. This way they are minimizing their costs and maximizing their profits. The components of a linear programming model are Vlookup, Sumif, If, Sumproduct. Vlookup searches for a specific number and places it in a certain column or row. Sumif finds the best possible outcome from the data given. Sumproduct multiplys the data given.
